race.description: Home Of Live Sport @ Port City Bowling Club Handicap
race.comment: MISS DEFY (7) turned things around last start and got the job done over 2000m at Taree. Drops back slightly in trip but is well placed to keep the ball rolling. RAISED BY WOLVES (15) made progress last time out, finishing second at the end of 1600m at Coffs Harbour after being in the firing line on the bend. Backs up quickly and is a two-time winner at this venue. Can give this a shake AMALFI AMORE (9) stuck on gamely into fifth last start over 2018m at Taree. Is another that is on the short turnaround and is worth keeping in mind. FIGHTING MAGNUS (1) showed good early dash and raced on the speed last start before fading to finish fourth at Taree. Worth including. STROBING (2) was better last time and should appreciate the rise in trip. Not without an each-way hope.
